This is what I have found to work well for the time being:

```python
cy_num = cy.fused_type(list, object)

@cy.cfunc
def _binary_func_internal(a: cy_num, b: cy_num):
    pass

def binary_func(a, b):
    tp1 = type(a)
    tp2 = type(b)
    if tp1 is list and tp2 is list:
        a1: list = a
        b1: list = b
        return _binary_func_internal(a1, b1)
    elif tp1 is list:
        a1: list = a
        return _binary_func_internal(a1, b)
    elif tp2 is list:
        b1: list = b
        return _binary_func_internal(a, b1)
    else:
        return _binary_func_internal(a, b)
```

Call time ends up comparable to the one as if no `fused_type` arguments were present. From 400ns down to 40ns.
